Fixing the ID and Passing OrigSuppNum
To pass OrigSuppNum from the current row into the ComboBox, you donâ€™t need to assign a hardcoded ID like OrigSuppNum.

Instead, bind the value of OrigSuppNum into the request parameters using .Data() â€” and ditch the hardcoded ID.

ðŸ”§ Update NscSupplierComboBox.cshtml
csharp
Copy
Edit
@(Html.Kendo().ComboBox()
    .Name(fieldName)
    .DataTextField("Text")
    .DataValueField("Text")
    .Filter(FilterType.Contains)
    .Placeholder("Enter supplier number...")
    .AutoBind(false)
    .MinLength(2)
    .HtmlAttributes(new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "data-column", fieldName }
    })
    .Events(e =>
    {
        e.Select("onNscPartsComboBoxSelect");
    })
    .DataSource(source =>
    {
        source.Read(read =>
        {
            read.Url(Url.Action("GetSupplierDetails", "AutoComplete"))
                .Type(HttpVerbs.Get)
                .Data("function() { return { supplierNumber: getSupplierNumber(this) }; }"); // <-- this part changed
        })
        .ServerFiltering(true);
    })
)
And in JS, define this function:

js
Copy
Edit
function getSupplierNumber(comboBox) {
    var row = comboBox.element.closest("tr");
    var grid = $("#NscPartsMaterialDetailsRebuiltPartsGrid").data("kendoGrid");
    var data = grid.dataItem(row);
    return data ? data.OrigSuppNum : "";
}
